<section>
<section id="slide-org9437aec">
<h2 id="org9437aec">2.1 â€“ Compare and contrast TCP and UDP ports, protocols, and their purposes.</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org9437aec">
</div>
<div class="slide-footer"><br></div>
</section>
<section id="slide-orge2544c4">
<h3 id="orge2544c4">Brief Introduction to IP</h3>
<ul>
<li>How do 1s and 0s move from one place to another over a network?</li>
<li>Brief reflection on the absurdity of sending all those poor 1s and 0s by themselves</li>
<li>We decided to put them in little boxes or <b>packets</b> that help them along their way</li>

</ul>
<div class="slide-footer"><br></div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org3d03c02">
<h3 id="org3d03c02">Sketch of some packets</h3>

<div class="figure">
<p><img src="./images/2-1-IPpacketSketch.png" alt="2-1-IPpacketSketch.png" height="100%">
</p>
<p><span class="figure-number">Figure 27: </span>Here are some packets</p>
</div>

<div class="slide-footer"><br></div>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgaa2301c">
<h3 id="orgaa2301c">TCP vs. UDP</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgaa2301c">
</div>
<div class="slide-footer"><br></div>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgf4ff978">
<h4 id="orgf4ff978"><b>TCP</b> - Transmission Control Protocol</h4>
<ul>
<li>&ldquo;Connection-oriented&rdquo; - every packet is checked for delivery</li>
<li><i>3-way handshake</i>:
<ol>
<li>SYN: client computer initiates connection with a synchronization request (SYN packet)</li>
<li>SYN + ACK: Server responds with a synchronization / acknowledgment packet</li>
<li>ACK: Client sends acknowledgment packet</li>

</ol></li>
<li>Then the connection is established - a <i>TCP socket connection</i></li>
<li>Every single packet is accounted for in TCP - flow control, etc</li>

</ul>
<div class="slide-footer"><br></div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org10c9ec4">
<h4 id="org10c9ec4"><b>UDP</b> - User Datagram Protocol</h4>
<ul>
<li>&ldquo;Connectionless sessions&rdquo; - if a packet is missed or dropped, no big deal</li>
<li>This can be faster - none of that back and forth</li>
<li>But no error-connection</li>
<li>Good for things that are streaming, like voice or media where a few dropped packets won&rsquo;t change much</li>

</ul>
<div class="slide-footer"><br></div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org5ac569d">
<h4 id="org5ac569d">A diagram of TCP &amp; UDP</h4>

<div class="figure">
<p><img src="./images/2-1-udp-tcpDiagram.jpg" alt="2-1-udp-tcpDiagram.jpg" width="88%">
</p>
<p><span class="figure-number">Figure 28: </span>A diagram of IP protocols</p>
</div>
<div class="slide-footer"><br></div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org6ee7891">
<h3 id="org6ee7891">Ports and Protocols</h3>
